<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left({2},-{3}\right)}</m></li><li><image width="52%"  pi:generated="problems/images/b5ea55f52cb09378091ecf75cb898852.png" />
</li></ul></p><p>The form of a parabola is <m>\displaystyle{y}={a}{\left({x}-{h}\right)}^{{2}}+{k}</m>. Because this parabola is <m>\displaystyle{y}={2}{\left({x}-{2}\right)}^{{2}}-{3}</m>, which can be written <m>\displaystyle{y}={2}{\left({x}-{\left({2}\right)}\right)}^{{2}}+{\left(-{3}\right)}</m> we know the following.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{h}={2}</m>, <m>\displaystyle{k}=-{3}</m>. Thus the vertex is <m>\displaystyle{\left({2},-{3}\right)}</m>.</p>
<p>To graph the parabola we can use the vertex and another convenient point. One convenient point is at <m>\displaystyle{x}={2}+{1}={3}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}={2}{\left({3}-{\left({2}\right)}\right)}^{{2}}+{\left(-{3}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle={2}{\left({1}\right)}^{{2}}+{\left(-{3}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle={2}+{\left(-{3}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle=-{1}</m>.</p>
<p>We use <m>\displaystyle{\left({3},-{1}\right)}</m>.</p>
</solution>
